  minicardTitle: 'Change the article',
  result: '',
  details: '<p>We listen to the beginning sound of the word following the indefinite articles <b>a</b> and <b>an</b>. If it sounds like a consonant, we use <b>a</b>. If it sounds like a vowel, we use <b>an</b>. Some letters can sound like a vowel or consonant. When the following word is an abbreviation, listen to how the abbreviation is spoken. We hear a vowel sound at the beginning of <i>MBA</i> (em-be-a) and a consonant sound at the beginning of <i>NASA</i>.\n',
